President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Eric D. Eberhard to the position of Member, Board of Trustees of the Morris K. Udall and Stewart L. Udall Foundation. Eberhard is currently a Distinguished Indian Law Practitioner in Residence and a Senior Fellow at the Center for Indian Law and Policy at the Seattle University School of Law. He also serves as an Associate Justice of the Court of Appeals of the Confederated Tribes of Coos, Lower Umpqua and Suislaw Indians in Oregon. Eberhard has a background in Indian law, having previously worked as General Counsel and Staff Director on the Senate Committee on Indian Affairs for Senator John McCain. He has also held positions within the Navajo Nation and has been involved with various Native American organizations. Eberhard received his B.A. from Western Reserve University, J.D. from the University of Cincinnati, and LL.M from the George Washington University.